  "prompt": "How do I deal with this new YouTube bug?",
  "response": "Okay, let's try to figure out what YouTube bug you're experiencing and how to troubleshoot it.  To help me give you the best advice, please tell me:\n\n**1. What is the specific bug you're experiencing?**\n\nThe more detail you can provide, the better.  For example:\n\n*   **Is it a playback issue?** (e.g., videos won't load, buffering problems, audio issues, video freezes, green screen)\n*   **Is it a UI/Interface problem?** (e.g., buttons don't work, layout is messed up, comments section is broken)\n*   **Is it an account-related issue?** (e.g., can't log in, subscriptions disappeared, watch history is gone)\n*   **Is it a feature-specific bug?** (e.g., live chat not working, can't create playlists, can't upload videos)\n*   **What error messages are you seeing (if any)?**  Write them down exactly.\n*   **When did you first notice the bug?**\n*   **Has the bug been consistent, or does it happen intermittently?**\n*   **What device are you using?** (e.g., computer, phone, tablet, smart TV, game console)\n*   **What operating system are you using?** (e.g., Windows 10/11, macOS, Android, iOS, tvOS)\n*   **What browser are you using?** (e.g., Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge) If you are using the app, specify that.\n*   **Are you using any browser extensions or ad blockers?**\n\n**2. What troubleshooting steps have you already tried?**\n\nThis will help me avoid suggesting things you've already done.  For example:\n\n*   Restarting your device\n*   Clearing your browser's cache and cookies\n*   Updating your browser or the YouTube app\n*   Checking your internet connection\n*   Trying a different browser or device\n*   Disabling browser extensions\n*   Logging out and back into your YouTube account\n*   Reinstalling the YouTube app\n\n**In the meantime, here are some general troubleshooting steps you can try, based on common YouTube problems:**\n\n**General Troubleshooting (Try these first):**\n\n*   **Check YouTube's Status:**  Sometimes YouTube itself is having problems.  Go to [DownDetector](https://downdetector.com/status/youtube/) or search on Twitter for \"#YouTubeDown\" to see if other people are reporting issues. If there is a widespread problem, you just have to wait for YouTube to fix it.\n*   **Restart Your Device:**  A simple restart can often resolve temporary glitches.\n*   **Check Your Internet Connection:**  Make sure you have a stable internet connection. Try running a speed test (e.g., Google Speed Test) to see if your connection is performing as expected.  Try restarting your modem and router.\n*   **Update Your Browser/App:**  Make sure you're using the latest version of your browser or the YouTube app.  Outdated software can cause compatibility issues.\n    *   **Browser:** Go to your browser's settings/menu and look for \"About [Browser Name]\" or \"Check for Updates.\"\n    *   **App (Android):** Open the Google Play Store, search for \"YouTube,\" and tap \"Update\" if available.\n    *   **App (iOS):** Open the App Store, tap your profile icon, and scroll down to see if there's an update for YouTube.\n*   **Clear Cache and Cookies (Browser):**  Cached data and cookies can sometimes cause problems.\n    *   **Chrome:**  Click the three dots in the top-right corner, go to More Tools > Clear Browsing Data.  Select \"Cookies and other site data\" and \"Cached images and files,\" then click \"Clear data.\"\n    *   **Firefox:** Click the three horizontal lines in the top-right corner, go to Options > Privacy & Security. In the \"Cookies and Site Data\" section, click \"Clear Data.\" Select \"Cookies and Site Data\" and \"Cached Web Content,\" then click \"Clear.\"\n    *   **Safari:** Go to Safari > Preferences > Privacy. Click \"Manage Website Data\" and then \"Remove All.\"\n    *   **Edge:** Click the three dots in the top-right corner, go to Settings > Privacy, search, and services. Under \"Clear browsing data,\" click \"Choose what to clear.\" Select \"Cookies and other site data\" and \"Cached images and files,\" then click \"Clear now.\"\n*   **Try a Different Browser/Device:**  This will help you determine if the problem is specific to your current browser/device.\n*   **Log Out and Back In:**  This can sometimes resolve account-related issues.\n*   **Disable Browser Extensions:**  Extensions can sometimes interfere with YouTube's functionality.  Try disabling them one by one to see if that fixes the problem.\n* **Try Incognito/Private Browsing Mode:** This will allow you to browse without any extensions or cookies and can help you determine if one of those is the issue.\n\n**Specific Troubleshooting (Based on potential issues):**\n\n*   **Playback Issues (Buffering, Freezing, etc.):**\n    *   **Lower Video Quality:**  Select a lower resolution (e.g., 480p or 360p) to reduce bandwidth requirements.\n    *   **Close Other Applications:**  Close any other programs or browser tabs that are using your internet connection.\n    *   **Update Graphics Drivers (Computer):** Outdated graphics drivers can cause video playback problems.  Go to your graphics card manufacturer's website (e.g., NVIDIA, AMD, Intel) to download the latest drivers.\n    *   **Hardware Acceleration:** In your browser's settings, try disabling or enabling hardware acceleration. This setting can sometimes cause conflicts.\n*   **UI/Interface Problems:**\n    *   **Zoom Level:** Make sure your browser's zoom level is set to 100%.  You can usually adjust the zoom level by pressing Ctrl + 0 (or Cmd + 0 on a Mac).\n    *   **Ad Blockers:** Sometimes ad blockers can interfere with the layout of websites. Try disabling your ad blocker or whitelisting YouTube.\n*   **Account-Related Issues:**\n    *   **Check Your Google Account:** Make sure your Google account is in good standing. Check for any security alerts or unusual activity.\n    *   **YouTube Premium:** If you have YouTube Premium, make sure your subscription is still active.\n\nOnce you provide more details about the bug you're experiencing, I can give you more specific advice. Good luck!\n",
